text: CYMEL U-216-8 resin is a partially n-butylated urea- formaldehyde crosslinking agent supplied in a blend of n-butanol and xylene. It possesses a lower molecular weight than most other butylated ureas, which contributes to its low bulk viscosity and high degree of hydrocarbon tolerance. CYMEL U-216-8 resin displays excellent compatibility with most hydrophobic resins, such as epoxies, and can contribute to improved leveling and adhesion characteristics. CYMEL U-216-8 resin is recommended as a crosslinking resin in primer coatings, can coatings, metal deco and wood cabinet finishes.

text: The properties of coatings based on Desmodur BL 4265 SN blocked polyisocyanate can be influenced, as with two-component polyurethane systems, by the degree of crosslinking and the choice of the polyol. The cure time and temperature required are also dependent upon the choice of coreactant. Combining Desmodur BL 4265 SN blocked polyisocyanate with hydroxyl-functional polyesters such as Desmophen 670 BA gives films with high flexibility and hard- ness. The cure rate can be varied by catalysis with- out adverse effects on storage. Crosslinking with polyamines or amides may result in limited storage stability. In coil coating systems, adequate crosslink- ing may be achieved without catalysis at 465ºF peak metal temperature (P.M.T.). With the addition of 1% dibutyl tin dilaurate (DBTDL) based on solid resin, a crosslinking temperature of 435ºF P.M.T. is possible. Thermal yellowing may occur at temperatures above 320ºF (160℃), depending on the baking time and the polyol used. Testing in Florida indicates that Desmo- dur BL 4265 SN blocked polyisocyanate provides excellent weather stability comparable to Desmodur N 3390A BA/SN polyisocyanate.

text: Properties and application: | Main properties of coatings formulated with POLURENE HR.B are fast curing and limited yellowing. In combination with POLURENE AD, POLURENE HR.B can be used for the formulation of sealers and matt, high gloss, clear and pigmented topcoat, when fast curing and high scratch resistance are required. In order to avoid film tightening and short pot life, when POLURENE HR.B is used as hardener, it is recommended accurately choosing the hydroxylated component. To avoid turbidity of solutions based on POLURENE HR.B during storage, it is advisable to limit the use of aromatic solvents like Xylene and Toluene and to keep a solid content over 30%. | Main properties of coatings formulated with POLURENE HR.B are fast curing and limited yellowing. In combination with POLURENE AD, POLURENE HR.B can be used for the formulation of sealers and matt, high gloss, clear and pigmented topcoat, when fast curing and high scratch resistance are required. In order to avoid film tightening and short pot life, when POLURENE HR.B is used as hardener, it is recommended accurately choosing the hydroxylated component. To avoid turbidity of solutions based on POLURENE HR.B during storage, it is advisable to limit the use of aromatic solvents like Xylene and Toluene and to keep a solid content over 30%.

text: Properties / Applications As corrosion-resistant primers, coatings based on Desmodur E 28 polyisocyanate can be formulated to contain zinc as zinc-rich primers that give galvanic protection. To ensure satisfactory intercoat adhesion, recoating intervals must be determined. The high NCO content of Desmodur E 28 also makes it an important curing agent for two-component systems. Desmodur E 28 polyisocyanate is an outstanding material for moisture-curing one-component formulations and is highly recommended to prime and seal porous substrates. Clear formulations of this type are effective dust-binding impregnants as well as sealers for cement and other substrates because they can protect the substrate from chemicals, deicing salt, and mineral oils.

text: RMFI SH Casco SG One of the consequences of non-observances of the safety advice could be allergic reaction. Detail are given in our Technical information Bulletin on the safety precaution to be observed on handling polyurethane raw materials, Owing to the low vapor pressure at the temperature and air changes normally encountered in the place of work, the concentration of MDI = diphenylmethane diisocyanate in the air will not be as high as the maximum allowable value*(TLV), viz. 0.01 ppm in BRD = 0.1 mg/m3 of air . At least 8 air changes per hour are recommended. A positive pressure fresh air breathing apparatus must be worn, or an efficient exhaust fan should be mounted on the spot, if isocyanate based on MDI are heated to above 40℃, if the mixing headed are being flushed with compressed air, or if rigid foam spray is being applied.
